0.1.0.description:
# Initial Release

This version only contains Tourist Trap and Cherry Blossom as courses and has no YAML settings. Energymaster's variant has linear course play logic, while MusicBlox's variant has non-linear practice mode logic.

0.1.1.description: Updated to the first version on the Discord

1.0.0.description:
A restructuring of the apworld that combines the previous 2 apworlds into one that lets you select logic from the yaml settings.

This update also includes all currently available courses as of release! You can pick which courses you want to play in the yaml via their acronym names. Be careful adding too many courses as this can balloon the world up to 2000+ checks!

Please make sure to read the readme to get a rundown on how this manual works.

Big big thank you to @MusicBlox for making the code that generates nearly our entire apworld from one course metadata csv!

And big thanks to @Fairweather-Furry for helping debug on Linux, helping me upkeep the course metadata, and making the little logo on top of our readme!

If anyone is on mac and has a problem generating please either create an issue here on github, dm me (energymaster) on discord, or leave a message in the Walkabout thread in the Manual for Archipelago discord server.
